data.name: BDC_CreateProfileDescription1
data.value: A profile page for the selected External Content Type(s) will be created on the indicated host site. A "View Profile" action will be created to point to the created profile page. The 'View Profile' Action will be used as the External Content Type Default Action.

data.name: BDC_CreateProfileDescription2
data.value: If a profile page already exists, re-creating it will overwrite the previous one, unless the profile host site has changed. Use caution when you choose to re-create the profile page, as previous customizations will be lost.

data.name: BDC_CreateProfileDescription3
data.value: In case that you have specified a Custom Action as the External Content Type Default Action, creating the profile page will change the Default Action to the 'View Profile' Action.

data.name: BDC_CreateProfileDescription4
data.value: In case of upgrade from SharePoint 2007, a "View Profile (SharePoint 2007)" action will be created. It will point to the location of the previous profile page. "View Profile" action will point to the newly created profile page.

data.name: BDC_SetProfilePageHost_PageTitle
data.value: Configure External Content Type Profile Page Host

data.name: BDC_SetProfilePageHost_PageDesc1
data.value: Specify a SharePoint site where profile pages of External Content Types will be created. You can update this site at any time. But we strongly recommend you use a single, dedicated SharePoint site to host the profile pages of all your External Content Types.

data.name: BDC_SetProfilePageHost_PageDesc2
data.value: Make sure you set up the permission of the SharePoint site correctly. For those who need to create profile pages, give them at minimum the "Design" permission, which allows "Add and Customize Pages" at the host site; You can also assign them to a SharePoint Group that has the "Design" permission. For end users, give read-only permission. If you need to create a new web application, please make sure you associate the web application with this Business Data Connectivity Shared Services Application.
